md:titleInfo.md:title: [Šarh] Dīwān Ğarīr ibn 'Atīyah (+ al-Šanfarā (d. ca. 550 CE ))

md:note.div:
Digtsamling med kommentar af Muhammad ibn Habīb al-Hāšimī og to enkelte digte henholdsvis af den før islamiske al-Šanfarā (tilskrevet) og af Abū Sa'īd al-Hasan ibn al-Husyn al-Sukkarī (d. 275 H [888]), kopieret i 1739 af Johann Jacob Reiske (1716-1774).
Håndskriftet [Šarh] Dīwān Ğarīr ibn 'Atīyah findes i Leiden Univetsitetsbibliotek, men er efter kopieringen af Reiske blevet stærkt beskadiget.
Cod. Arab. 250

Poetry collection with a commentary by Muhammad ibn Habīb al-Hāšimī and two poems ascribed to the pre-Islamic poet al-Šanfarā and to Abū Sa'īd al-Hasan ibn al-Husyn al-Sukkarī (d. 275 H [888]), copied in 1739 by Johann Jacob Reiske (1716-1774 CE).
The manuscript [Šarh] Dīwān Ğarīr ibn 'Atīyah is in Leiden Univetsity Library, but have been damaged after the copying by Reiske in 1739.
Cod. Arab. 250
